"I say, Frieda," exclaimed her husband;
                        "it's been too much for you. A drop of brandy, my
                        dear,"

Out of every nook and cranny in the land oozed constant and reliable reports
                        from the most trustworthy sources, from agents of both sexes; sly, secret,
                        mysterious forces supplied them with facts that no man was supposed to know;
                        the magic of the Far East was surpassed by these wizards who came not out of
                        Egypt but from commonplace, unromantic circles in the Occident.
